Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Pat @bavette steak{10%ounce}(sliced into ½-inch strips) dry with #paper towels{}.

> Simply cook through this step as instructed, swapping in steak for chicken.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak, scallion whites, and @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}. Cook until steak is browned and cooked through and scallions are slightly softened, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside. Wash out pan.

Place @flour tortillas{2} on a clean work surface. Evenly sprinkle @pepper jack cheese{1/2%cup} onto one half of each tortilla. Top with steak filling, then sprinkle with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}. Fold tortillas in half to create quesadillas.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for filling over medium heat. Add quesadillas and cook until tortillas are golden brown and cheese melts, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.

Cut quesadillas into wedges and divide between plates. Sprinkle with reserved scallion greens. Serve with @smoky red pepper crema{2%tbsp} on the side.